            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " A similar bilinear form  $F_K$  can be defined for an arbitrary convex body K. Since  $V_n(TL_1, ..., TL_n) =$   $|det(T)|V_n(L_1,...,L_n)$  (for any  $n$ -tuple of convex bodies  $(L_i)$ , and any affine transform T), non-negativity of  $F_K$  is an affine invariant property. In 2018, Saroglou, Soprunov and Zvavitch obtained acharacterization of  $n$ -simplices among polytopes :",
            "line_with_spans": [
