            "text": " Several necessary conditions (for  $F_K \\geq 0$  to hold) were derived :  $K$  cannot be decomposable, nor weakly decomposable (see [\\[SSZ2](#SSZ2), Def 5.3] where this notion was introduced), the surface area measure  $S_K$  cannot have a regular direction<sup>1</sup> in its support (see [\\[SSZ2](#SSZ2), Prop 4.2]),  $K$  cannot have infinitely many facets on its boundary. We refer to [\\[SZ16\\]](#SZ16), [\\[SSZ1\\]](#SSZ1), [\\[SSZ2\\]](#SSZ2) for proofs, and comments on these conditions.",
