            "text": " **Theorem 2.** Let K be a convex body such that K has a facet F satisfying:  $Isop(F) > Isop(K)$ . Then  $F_K \\ge 0$  doesn't hold : there exists a pair of convex bodies  $(A, B) \\in (\\mathcal{K}^n)^2$  such that  $F_K(A, B) < 0$ .",
