            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " A classical result due to Minkowski [Mink] states that, for any  $m \\geq 2$ , and any m-tuple  $(K_1, ..., K_m)$  of compact convex sets in  $\\mathbb{R}^n$ , the volume of the Minkowski sum  $\\sum \\lambda_i K_i$ , is a polynomial in the  $\\lambda_i \\geq 0$ . More precisely, Minkowski's theorem asserts there exists coefficients  $c_a \\geq 0$ , indexed by *m*-tuples  $a = (a_1, ..., a_m) \\in \\mathbb{N}^m$  summing to *n* (i.e.  $|a| = a_1 + ... + a_m = n$ ), which only depend on  $(K_1, ..., K_m)$ , and such that, for any  $\\lambda_1, ..., \\lambda_m \\geq 0$ :",
            "line_with_spans": [
